# code_highlight.lt -- In HTML mode mdlout routes language-tagged
# code blocks through @SVG so the browser sees a real <pre><code
# class="language-XXX"> that highlight.js can colour. In PDF/PS mode
# (this snippet's mode) mdlout falls back to @Verbatim so the code
# still renders as monospaced text on the printed page. This snippet
# pins the PDF/PS form.
@SysInclude { doc }
@Doc @Text @Begin
@PP
A code block with a language hint:
@LP
@IndentedDisplay @F @Verbatim @Begin
def hello():
    print("hi")
@End @Verbatim
@PP
Text resumes normally after the verbatim block.
@End @Text
